Package project3.three

Class Summary
DatalogProgram The Parser portion of the Datalog Program.
DatalogSegment A DatalogSegment is an abstract classs that is differentiated from List by having a name.
Domain The domain (set of valid values or constants) for a datalog program.
Fact A Fact is a NamedList of Constants.
FactList A list of Fact.
Head The Head of a Rule.
List The generalized List class.
Location Defines the location of an argument in a simple predicate of a predicate list.
Locations For every variable in a predicate list we need to store the locations of where that variable appears (there can be more than one).
LocationsAndValue For every variable in a predicate list we need to store the locations of where that variable appears (there can be more than one) and store the value for the variable.
NamedList A List with an associated name.
Node The parser builds a parse tree of nodes.
Predicate A Predicate is a named list of Arguments.
Project3 The root of Project 3.
Query A Query in the datalog program.
QueryList A list of Query.
QueryVariableInformation The information about each variable in a Query.
Rule A Rule in the datalog program.
Scheme A scheme is a named list of Constants.
SchemeList A list of Scheme.
SetOfSolutions For every query we keep of list a solutions that make the query true.
VariableInformation The information about each variable in a PredicateList (and a Query since it is a PredicateList).
 

Enum Summary
List.LengthConstraint These are the different types of length contraints we can impose on a list.
 

Exception Summary
ParserException A special type of exception for parser problems.
